The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 24 March is 253,841 (29,256.7 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 19 March, there were 9,922 new confirmed cases (1,143.6 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 12 March, there were 8,056 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 23% (1,866 extra cases).
